.SH "NAME"
is_etherdev_addr \- Tell if given Ethernet address belongs to the device\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'bool\ is_etherdev_addr('u
.BI "bool is_etherdev_addr(const\ struct\ net_device\ *\ " "dev" ", const\ u8\ " "addr[6\ +\ 2]" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdev\fR
.RS 4
Pointer to a device structure
.RE
.PP
\fIaddr[6 + 2]\fR
.RS 4
Pointer to a six\-byte array containing the Ethernet address
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Compare passed address with all addresses of the device\&. Return true if the address if one of the device addresses\&.
.PP
Note that this function calls
\fBether_addr_equal_64bits\fR
so take care of the right padding\&.
